    "teacher_markdown": "**Error Type**: Syntax Error (Code won’t run due to a typo)\r\n\r\n**Expected Outcome**: The `Painter` should move forward and paint a red and green tile.\r\n\r\nDebugging Challenge\r\n\r\n- The program throws an `AttributeError` because `.painter()` and `.pant()` are not a valid `Painter` methods.\r\n- Students must determine what’s wrong with these method calls and correct them.\r\n- Hint for students: Carefully check function and method names.",
